beer.beer_description: Medium bodied amber lager that was the beer originally served at Oktoberfest until it was replaced by the lighter, hoppier Festbier. Historically, Marzens were brewed in March and lagered in cold caves over the German summer to be ready for the festival. Days Gone By showcases the rich, toasty and bready flavours of German Munich malt.

Thanks to every one of you for making this beautifully diverse community what it is today! Let’s raise our glasses, check in a brew, earn this badge, and cheers to the next 14 years of memories with you! For extra credit, be sure to check out the latest Hop Culture piece on the beers with most 5-star check-ins on Untappd so far in 2024.
